tags.name: lrnsys-progress-circle
tags.description:
`lrnsys-progress-circle`

Events:

  * `node-percent-milestone` - 

  * `node-is-active` - 

  * `node-status-change` - 

Attributes:

  * `value` {`number`} - Current value.

  * `tool-tip` {`boolean`} - Whether to add a tooltip on hover.

  * `list-view` {`boolean`} - If this is in a list view, expand the output.

  * `icon` {`string`} - Icon.

  * `icon-complete` {`string`} - Special icon to use when the item has been completed.

  * `loading-icon` {`string`} - Loading icon

  * `finished-icon` {`string`} - Finished icon

  * `active-icon` {`string`} - Current value.

  * `step` {`number`} - Array position within a larger body of items.

  * `active` {`boolean`} - If this item is active or not in the larger list

  * `status` {`string`} - Status of the progression.
Possible values are disabled, loading, available, complete

  * `disabled` {`boolean`} - Correctly disable the button if it's status is such.

  * `loading` {`boolean`} - Calculate if something is in a loading status which invokes a swirl.

  * `finished` {`boolean`} - Boolean to invoke "finished" state. Useful for the last circle
in a series.

  * `max` {`string`} - Max progression for doing math against.

  * `__chimed` {`boolean`} - Internal property to ensure we only ding 1x

  * `__finishchimed` {`boolean`} - Internal property to ensure we only finish 1x

  * `url` {`string`} - URL to link to on click.

  * `data-url` {`string`} - Data url to bubble up for more advanced implementations.

  * `stroke-width` {`number`} - Stroke width.

  * `focus-state` {`boolean`} - Tracks if focus state is applied for element consistency
when dealing with focus vs hover states.

  * `play-sound` {`boolean`} - Play sound status; if this should play sound
when it hits certain milestones or not.

  * `play-finish-sound` {`boolean`} - Play sound at end; if this should play sound
when it hits certain milestones or not.

  * `complete-sound` {`string`} - Play sound on complete.

  * `finished-sound` {`string`} - Play sound on complete.

  * `_bubble-progress` - Fire and track milestones towards completion state.

Properties:

tags.name: lrnsys-progress
tags.description:
`lrnsys-progress`

Events:

  * `progress-state-change` - 

  * `progress-response-loaded` - 

  * `json-outline-schema-active-item-changed` - 

  * `node-load-failed` - 

Attributes:

  * `disable-ajax-calls` {`boolean`} - Disable internal ajax calls as something is handling them above.

  * `items` {`any[]`} - Items to display to visualize the progression.

  * `sound` {`boolean`} - Play sounds whenever an item is complete.
This can get pretty annoying though unless the items
won't be completed for awhile.

  * `sound-finish` {`boolean`} - Play sound when the user finishes the progression. This
could also be annoying but far less so :)

  * `complete-sound` {`string`} - Play sound on complete.

  * `finished-sound` {`string`} - Play sound on complete.

  * `title` {`string`} - Title of this progression, primarily for accessibility.

  * `key-items` {`any[]`} - Items displayed at specific points on the progression.
These aren't filled up but place points along the progression
which can help people see where they are relative to other
factors such as % complete as a tick mark or icon.

  * `active` {`number`} - ID of the active item.

  * `progressive-unlock` {`boolean`} - Whether to automatically make disabled items available
or not when the previous one was just complete.

  * `state` {`string`} - State of progress in the current progression

  * `overall-percentage` {`number`} - How far is the user through this series of items.

  * `_response-list` {`any[]`} - Responses for each item.

  * `active-node-response` {`string`} - Active response from the node selected.

  * `manifest` - Active response from the node selected.

  * `node-data-error` - Error.

  * `vertical` {`boolean`} - Flag to be vertical instead of horizontal.

  * `size` {`string`} - Size to make everything, small, medium, large, and epic
are available class names; default medium.

  * `stroke-width` {`number`} - Calculate width based on the size since we have to convert em to px.

Properties:

  * `items` {`any[]`} - Items to display to visualize the progression.

  * `sound` {`boolean`} - Play sounds whenever an item is complete.
This can get pretty annoying though unless the items
won't be completed for awhile.

  * `soundFinish` {`boolean`} - Play sound when the user finishes the progression. This
could also be annoying but far less so :)

  * `completeSound` {`string`} - Play sound on complete.

  * `finishedSound` {`string`} - Play sound on complete.

  * `title` {`string`} - Title of this progression, primarily for accessibility.

  * `keyItems` {`any[]`} - Items displayed at specific points on the progression.
These aren't filled up but place points along the progression
which can help people see where they are relative to other
factors such as % complete as a tick mark or icon.

  * `active` {`number`} - ID of the active item.

  * `progressiveUnlock` {`boolean`} - Whether to automatically make disabled items available
or not when the previous one was just complete.

  * `state` {`string`} - State of progress in the current progression

  * `overallPercentage` {`number`} - How far is the user through this series of items.

  * `_responseList` {`any[]`} - Responses for each item.

  * `activeNodeResponse` {`string`} - Active response from the node selected.

  * `manifest` - Active response from the node selected.

  * `nodeDataError` - Error.

  * `vertical` {`boolean`} - Flag to be vertical instead of horizontal.

  * `size` {`string`} - Size to make everything, small, medium, large, and epic
are available class names; default medium.

  * `strokeWidth` {`number`} - Calculate width based on the size since we have to convert em to px.
